{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Large language models pre-trained on generic texts serve as the foundation upon which most state-of-the-art Natural language Processing (NLP) models are built.",
    "There is ample evidence that, for certain domains and downstream tasks, models that are pre-trained on specialised data outperform baselines that have only relied on generic texts (Sanh et al. 2019; Alsentzer et al. 2019; Beltagy, Lo, and Cohan 2019; Nguyen, Vu, and Nguyen 2020; Chalkidis et al. 2020).",
    "These models, however, are heavy in size and number of parameters, making them unsuitable for devices with limited memory and processing capacity.",
    "Furthermore, the rate at which leading technology corporations build these progressively larger and more resource-intensive models is a subject of debate in the Artificial Intelligence (AI) community (Bender et al. 2021), and there is interest in developing methods that would make these tools more accessible by creating smaller and faster versions of them that would run reasonably well on smaller devices (Li et al. 2020; Schick and Schütze 2021).",
    "This would allow independent researchers, particularly those from lowincome nations, to contribute to the advancement of AI."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "There is ample evidence that, for certain domains and downstream tasks, models that are pre-trained on specialised data outperform baselines that have only relied on generic texts (Sanh et al. 2019; Alsentzer et al. 2019; Beltagy, Lo, and Cohan 2019; Nguyen, Vu, and Nguyen 2020; Chalkidis et al. 2020).",
    "Furthermore, the rate at which leading technology corporations build these progressively larger and more resource-intensive models is a subject of debate in the Artificial Intelligence (AI) community (Bender et al. 2021), and there is interest in developing methods that would make these tools more accessible by creating smaller and faster versions of them that would run reasonably well on smaller devices (Li et al. 2020; Schick and Schütze 2021)."
  ]
}